[INTRO]
[Sound: Distant temple bell rings once. Wind sound. A flute plays a slow, melancholic melody. A harmonium drone underneath. Then a distorted electric guitar riff cuts in, sharp and complex, playing a math‑rock pattern. Traditional large drum hits on every fourth beat, like a heartbeat. The sound of a crowd cheering and a keyboard click fades in and out.]

[Spoken whisper, layered with reverb]
From the roof of the world…
We carry the weight of the sky.
From the birthplace of light…
We rise.

[VERSE 1]
[Instrumental: Clean electric guitar arpeggios with math‑rock syncopation. Traditional small drum adds rolling patterns. Flute weaves a folk‑inspired melody. Bass guitar drives with a steady pulse.]

[Vocals: clear, powerful female]
Under Everest’s shadow, where the eagles dare
A dream was born in a Kathmandu square
Fingers on the keys, a silent prayer
A warrior forged from the mountain air

From the hills of Ilam to the peaks of Dhaulagiri
We carry the spirit of the yeti’s lair
In every lane, in every fight we share
The blood of a thousand ancestors runs there

[PRE-CHORUS 1]
[Instrumental: Drums build with traditional large drum and rock drums together. Brass horns enter with a short, rising fanfare. Guitar feedback swells. Flute holds a long, tense note.]

[Vocals: strained, emotional]
They said the snow would bury us
They said our hands were made for stone
But in our veins, the rivers rush
And we were never meant to be alone

[CHORUS 1]
[Instrumental: Full band explosion. Distorted guitar plays a soaring hook. Traditional large drum and rock drums lock in polyrhythm. Brass horns play a triumphant, celebratory melody. Flute doubles the guitar hook. Ambient synth pads create a vast space.]

[Vocals: soaring, anthemic]
This is the mountain calling
A thunder in the sky
We are the sons of Sagarmatha
We never die

From Lumbini’s light to the eastern sea
We are the legends, wild and free
Himalayan rising, feel the fire
Higher!

[POST-CHORUS]
[Instrumental: Music drops to just flute and clean guitar playing a catchy hook. Traditional small drum hits on the offbeat. Brass horns echo the hook softly.]

[Vocals: layered harmonies, wordless]
Ah, ah, ah…
The echo in the valley
Ah, ah, ah…
The roar of the rally

[VERSE 2]
[Instrumental: Returns to intricate math‑rock style. Guitar tapping, bass syncopated. Flute plays fragmented melody. Traditional large drum adds deep thuds.]

[Vocals: determined, faster]
A cable swings like a prayer flag in the breeze
A Gusion’s combo, lightning through the trees
A tank who stands like a stone in the stream
We are the heroes living the dream

From the Thamel streets to the world’s bright stage
We write our names in a digital age
With the heart of a Buddha, the roar of a storm
We break the limits, we transform

[PRE-CHORUS 2]
[Instrumental: Same build as first pre‑chorus, but with more urgency. Brass horns play a longer fanfare. Crowd chanting sample rises.]

[Vocals: half-whispered, intense]
For the kids who dream in the dark
For the mothers who pray at the temple gate
We will leave our mark
We will defy our fate

[CHORUS 2]
[Instrumental: Same as chorus 1 but with extra layers. Guitar solo begins in the background, raw and emotional. Brass horns add a counter‑melody. Flute soars with ornamented runs.]

[Vocals: powerful, layered harmonies]
This is the mountain calling
A thunder in the sky
We are the sons of Sagarmatha
We never die

From Lumbini’s light to the eastern sea
We are the legends, wild and free
Himalayan rising, feel the fire
Higher!

[BRIDGE]
[Instrumental: Sudden drop to silence. A solo flute plays a slow, mournful melody. Harmonium drone. Traditional large drum hits every eight seconds. Temple bells. Wind.]

[Vocals: intimate, spoken]
From the soil where the Buddha walked
From the snow that never melts
We draw the strength to rise again
To face the worlds we’ve felt

[Music begins to swell. A single electric guitar note sustained. Traditional large drum starts heartbeat again.]

[Chant: multiple voices, low and resolute]
We are the children of the Himalaya
We are the guardians of the light
We will not falter
We will not break

[FINAL CHORUS]
[Instrumental: Climax. Everything at full power. Distorted guitar, brass horns, traditional drums, rock drums, flute, harmonium, synth pads all together. Guitar solo weeps and screams. Flute solo answers. The crowd cheering is overwhelming.]

[Vocals: full anthemic, with gang vocals]
This is the mountain calling!
A thunder in the sky!
We are the sons of Sagarmatha!
We never die!

From Lumbini’s light to the eastern sea!
We are the legends, wild and free!
Himalayan rising, feel the fire!
Higher! Higher!
Himalayan rising—take us higher!

[OUTRO]
[Instrumental: The full band cuts abruptly. A solo flute plays the opening melody, now peaceful. A single traditional large drum hit. Temple bell. Wind. The sound of a keyboard click and a fading crowd cheer.]

[Whisper]
From the roof of the world…
We rise.

[Silence.]